<p>One of the great delights in life is entertaining family and friends to a sumptuous afternoon tea at home &ndash; and it all starts with a perfectly laid table featuring only the very best linen, crockery and cutlery. </p>
<p>Heather &amp; March is highly experienced in sourcing tip-top items from the best tableware producers in Europe, and during August is presenting three beautiful accoutrements for tea exclusively at its LANDMARK PRINCES store &ndash; a cake server, dinner knife and pie server from Ercuis of France. </p>
<p>Founded in 1861, Ercuis is acknowledged as one of the world&rsquo;s best silversmiths, embodying excellence in French craftsmanship, history and design. The company works with top designers in a range of fields, and is found in some of the world&rsquo;s most famous hotels and restaurants, as well as houses and yachts of the rich and famous.</p>
<p>The cake server comes from the Du Barry collection, decorated with fancy acanthus leaves, typical of the Louis XV style &ndash; a romantic and exuberant combination. The dinner knife and pie server are part of the Baguette collection, which emphasises pure and rounded lines; both are inspired by traditional shapes but adapted for modern living. All these French-made pieces are silver plated and dishwasher safe &ndash; and they bring refined elegance to the table when you&rsquo;re serving savoury or sweet pies and delicious cakes. </p>

